00:09:56.980 --> 00:10:00.580
The first thing is we know that
a really good way for users

00:10:00.580 --> 00:10:02.080
to understand what
your app is about

00:10:02.080 --> 00:10:04.760
is to show them a
video of the app.

00:10:04.760 --> 00:10:06.910
And this is why
earlier this year, we

00:10:06.910 --> 00:10:10.420
introduced a new feature,
a click-to-play video

00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:13.240
ad in Google Play.

00:10:13.240 --> 00:10:15.700
Now, this unit is
exactly like it says.

00:10:15.700 --> 00:10:18.430
Users go to the Google Play
store looking for some app

00:10:18.430 --> 00:10:19.210
to download.

00:10:19.210 --> 00:10:23.420
They're invited to watch a video
about an app they might like.

00:10:23.420 --> 00:10:24.910
And after watching
that video, they

00:10:24.910 --> 00:10:28.210
can decide whether they want
to download the app or not.

00:10:28.210 --> 00:10:32.870
This leads to very qualified
users for that advertiser.

00:10:37.760 --> 00:10:38.260
Sorry.

00:10:41.210 --> 00:10:43.640
Now, another way to
qualify high value users

00:10:43.640 --> 00:10:47.540
is to actually let them try
the app before they install it.

00:10:47.540 --> 00:10:49.040
And I'm sure many
of you have heard

00:10:49.040 --> 00:10:52.700
of this new technology called
Google Play Instant, which

00:10:52.700 --> 00:10:53.660
is really cool.

00:10:53.660 --> 00:10:55.920
Basically, if you haven't
heard about this technology,

00:10:55.920 --> 00:10:59.810
it allows you to build a
small version of your game

00:10:59.810 --> 00:11:03.800
and have it load instantly
for consumers to try.

00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:06.560
Now, how does this work with
Universal App Campaigns?

00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:07.880
Very simply.

00:11:07.880 --> 00:11:11.870
We are going to show users
a Try Now button in the app

00:11:11.870 --> 00:11:13.850
install ads that they encounter.

00:11:13.850 --> 00:11:16.190
So if you're using
Google Play Instant,

00:11:16.190 --> 00:11:18.380
you plug it into
Universal App Campaigns,

00:11:18.380 --> 00:11:20.660
and now users get a
try now experience

00:11:20.660 --> 00:11:22.670
where they get to
experience, potentially,

00:11:22.670 --> 00:11:25.990
a level of your game before
deciding to download.

00:11:25.990 --> 00:11:28.299
And this is something we're
actively experimenting with

00:11:28.299 --> 00:11:29.840
and will launch in
the coming months.

