00:15:11.850 --> 00:15:15.180
How exactly do I make the
most from my ad partners?

00:15:15.180 --> 00:15:16.930
How do I maximize revenue?

00:15:16.930 --> 00:15:19.500
Those are the two problems
that we want to help you with.

00:15:19.500 --> 00:15:22.440
Let's start with
great ads experiences.

00:15:22.440 --> 00:15:24.660
Now, stepping back
for a second, I've

00:15:24.660 --> 00:15:27.210
been working on apps
for six, seven years,

00:15:27.210 --> 00:15:28.950
and I've been really,
really interested

00:15:28.950 --> 00:15:31.200
with the emergence of
so many different ways

00:15:31.200 --> 00:15:33.240
that users can pay for things.

00:15:33.240 --> 00:15:35.110
They can pay through
subscriptions.

00:15:35.110 --> 00:15:36.900
They can pay through
in-app purchases.

00:15:36.900 --> 00:15:39.120
They can pay through
virtual currencies.

00:15:39.120 --> 00:15:41.400
And now there's other
things like tipping.

00:15:41.400 --> 00:15:42.960
There's just so
many different ways

00:15:42.960 --> 00:15:46.380
that monetization is
emerging in the apps surface.

00:15:46.380 --> 00:15:48.990
And one thing that we've
seen become very popular

00:15:48.990 --> 00:15:52.560
recently is hybrid
monetization, which

00:15:52.560 --> 00:15:55.380
is just a fancy way of
saying in-app purchases

00:15:55.380 --> 00:15:57.180
and ads in the same app.

00:15:59.730 --> 00:16:02.010
And when app developers
are doing this,

00:16:02.010 --> 00:16:04.140
one thing that's become
very popular recently

00:16:04.140 --> 00:16:06.240
is something called
rewarded ads.

00:16:06.240 --> 00:16:08.490
For those of you who don't
know what rewarded ads are,

00:16:08.490 --> 00:16:12.510
very simply, users opt
into watching an ad,

00:16:12.510 --> 00:16:16.760
and in return, they get
a service in the app.

00:16:16.760 --> 00:16:18.510
Now, this is very,
very popular in games,

00:16:18.510 --> 00:16:21.930
but I'll share a non-game
example, Pandora.

00:16:21.930 --> 00:16:24.540
Pandora realized
that many users who

00:16:24.540 --> 00:16:26.820
were using their
music service were not

00:16:26.820 --> 00:16:29.250
going to become subscribers.

00:16:29.250 --> 00:16:31.820
So instead they offered
those users a choice.

00:16:31.820 --> 00:16:35.160
Would you like to watch
an ad and in return get

00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:37.380
some ad free listening?

00:16:37.380 --> 00:16:40.020
And by and large, this is
an incredibly great model,

00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:44.190
because Pandora gets to monetize
those users who are not paying,

00:16:44.190 --> 00:16:47.220
and the user gets a service,
they're happy with it,

00:16:47.220 --> 00:16:51.810
and the advertiser actually gets
a very engaged and qualified

00:16:51.810 --> 00:16:55.070
view from that user.

00:16:55.070 --> 00:16:58.600
So let's take a look at a
second example, Avid.ly,

00:16:58.600 --> 00:17:01.810
which is a creator of a
game called Bingo Party.

00:17:01.810 --> 00:17:06.328
Now, Avid.ly was very concerned
about adding ads to their app.

00:17:06.328 --> 00:17:07.869
They were worried
that ads were going

00:17:07.869 --> 00:17:10.660
to ruin the gameplay
experience, that users

00:17:10.660 --> 00:17:13.450
would flee to other free games.

00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:15.369
So they decided to
try rewarded ads,

00:17:15.369 --> 00:17:17.170
just to see how it would work.

00:17:17.170 --> 00:17:21.760
And the surprising results are,
number one, they made more.

00:17:21.760 --> 00:17:27.970
They got an increase in revenue
between IAP and ads by 40%.

00:17:27.970 --> 00:17:30.520
But in addition,
session duration

00:17:30.520 --> 00:17:34.900
grew by 20%, which means that
by adding these ads to the game,

00:17:34.900 --> 00:17:38.200
users actually paid
more and played longer.

00:17:38.200 --> 00:17:40.000
So everybody wins, right?

00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:42.340
Avid.ly, Pandora are
showcasing that when

00:17:42.340 --> 00:17:46.000
you put the ads into the app
in an elegant way, users,

00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:48.080
publishers, advertisers
are all going to win.

00:17:50.620 --> 00:17:52.880
And because this model
has become very popular,

00:17:52.880 --> 00:17:56.530
it's no surprise that we have
seen rewarded ads in AdMob

00:17:56.530 --> 00:18:02.050
grow by 9x since we introduced
it in March of last year.

00:18:02.050 --> 00:18:05.134
And we've added a lot more
to rewarded ads since then.

00:18:05.134 --> 00:18:06.550
One of the things
that we've added

00:18:06.550 --> 00:18:08.590
is rewarded with
multiple options.

00:18:08.590 --> 00:18:11.320
And that's what you see
on this screen here.

00:18:11.320 --> 00:18:13.690
Essentially, users are
deciding to watch an ad

00:18:13.690 --> 00:18:16.870
to get some item or
service in the app.

00:18:16.870 --> 00:18:19.900
Why don't you let them pick
which ad they want to watch?

00:18:19.900 --> 00:18:22.360
This leads, again, to the
user being more interested

00:18:22.360 --> 00:18:24.490
in the ad that they've
decided to watch,

00:18:24.490 --> 00:18:28.960
and also the advertisers getting
a much more qualified user.

00:18:28.960 --> 00:18:34.925
This also then leads to higher
CPMs for you as a developer.

00:18:34.925 --> 00:18:37.050
Now, one of the new things
I'd like to share today,

00:18:37.050 --> 00:18:40.950
I'm really excited about, is
rewarded reporting in AdMob.

00:18:40.950 --> 00:18:44.430
Now, this may not sound like,
wow, what's going on here?

00:18:44.430 --> 00:18:46.270
Reported reporting
is super important,

00:18:46.270 --> 00:18:49.050
because you need to know
how rewarded actually

00:18:49.050 --> 00:18:51.160
works in your app.

00:18:51.160 --> 00:18:53.340
So here we're going to
share a lot more metrics

00:18:53.340 --> 00:18:56.220
about exactly what's going
on with the users that

00:18:56.220 --> 00:18:58.980
are interacting with
your rewarded ads, which

00:18:58.980 --> 00:19:02.940
rewarded ads are working and
not, what reward units are more

00:19:02.940 --> 00:19:05.550
resonating with users, what
are the view through rates

00:19:05.550 --> 00:19:06.730
of reward ads.

00:19:06.730 --> 00:19:09.190
And this lets you
as a developer tune

00:19:09.190 --> 00:19:13.230
and optimize how and where you
offer these rewards and also

00:19:13.230 --> 00:19:15.419
what reward to provide to users.

00:19:15.419 --> 00:19:17.460
This also gives you a
sense of how it's affecting

00:19:17.460 --> 00:19:19.260
your core user experience.

00:19:19.260 --> 00:19:22.320
Is it additive, like the
case we saw with Avid.ly?

00:19:22.320 --> 00:19:24.510
And how is it
affecting your RPU?

00:19:24.510 --> 00:19:27.090
So this is going to be
available in AdMob very soon.

00:19:30.460 --> 00:19:33.952
Now, I just talked about
great ads experiences in apps.

00:19:33.952 --> 00:19:36.410
Let me talk about something
else which is really important,

00:19:36.410 --> 00:19:38.600
which is maximizing
the revenue that you're

00:19:38.600 --> 00:19:42.310
getting from your ad partners.

00:19:42.310 --> 00:19:44.520
So typically the
way this works today

00:19:44.520 --> 00:19:46.530
is something called mediation.

00:19:46.530 --> 00:19:49.350
And very simply,
this is the ordering

00:19:49.350 --> 00:19:53.010
of how you sell your ads
to different ad partners.

00:19:53.010 --> 00:19:56.460
Now, mediation traditionally
works on a historical pricing

00:19:56.460 --> 00:20:00.150
basis, which basically means,
in this mock up you see here,

00:20:00.150 --> 00:20:03.540
Network A paid $2 in the
past, so they're at the top.

00:20:03.540 --> 00:20:05.550
And Network B and
Network C are below that,

00:20:05.550 --> 00:20:08.760
because historically
their prices were lower.

00:20:08.760 --> 00:20:11.040
Now, the flaw with this
model, as you can see,

00:20:11.040 --> 00:20:14.340
is that at any given
moment, each impression

00:20:14.340 --> 00:20:15.750
can be priced differently.

00:20:15.750 --> 00:20:17.700
And in fact,
Network B or C might

00:20:17.700 --> 00:20:20.130
have a higher price
for an impression

00:20:20.130 --> 00:20:22.270
than Network A at any time.

00:20:24.910 --> 00:20:26.220
So we think we can help.

00:20:26.220 --> 00:20:30.420
Earlier this year, we announced
a feature called Open Bidding.

00:20:30.420 --> 00:20:33.960
Now, what Open Bidding does is
it takes mediation and instead

00:20:33.960 --> 00:20:38.140
moves it to a real time
bidded auction system.

00:20:38.140 --> 00:20:39.000
What does that mean?

00:20:39.000 --> 00:20:43.230
Very simply, every impression is
available for every ad network

00:20:43.230 --> 00:20:46.870
to bid into simultaneously
and in real time.

00:20:46.870 --> 00:20:49.050
And this means a
higher and better price

00:20:49.050 --> 00:20:51.300
for each and every
impression for those of you

00:20:51.300 --> 00:20:55.350
who are selling ads
inventory in your apps.

00:20:55.350 --> 00:20:58.260
Now, the benefits are
beyond pricing as well.

00:20:58.260 --> 00:21:01.560
Mediation typically requires
integration of multiple ad

00:21:01.560 --> 00:21:05.730
network SDKs, as well as
launching multiple surfaces

00:21:05.730 --> 00:21:08.385
to reconcile billing and
figuring out payments.

00:21:10.900 --> 00:21:13.420
With Open Bidding, we're
trying to resolve all that.

00:21:13.420 --> 00:21:15.640
You can get most of the
[INAUDIBLE] benefits from all

00:21:15.640 --> 00:21:19.630
of those ad providers
through a single AdMob SDK,

00:21:19.630 --> 00:21:22.520
leading to a lighter app
for your users to download,

00:21:22.520 --> 00:21:25.330
and also less development time.

00:21:25.330 --> 00:21:27.490
And what's more,
AdMob will often

00:21:27.490 --> 00:21:30.310
manage the billing to
and provide transparency

00:21:30.310 --> 00:21:31.670
into your metrics.

00:21:31.670 --> 00:21:34.060
So you don't have to
chase down payments or log

00:21:34.060 --> 00:21:35.360
into multiple interfaces.

