00:22:01.340 --> 00:22:04.630
Now, let's talk about a second
way for maximizing revenue

00:22:04.630 --> 00:22:08.290
from your ad partners, something
called open measurement.

00:22:08.290 --> 00:22:11.530
And very, very simply,
brand advertisers

00:22:11.530 --> 00:22:14.020
are often buying
impressions for users,

00:22:14.020 --> 00:22:16.960
and they want to make sure that
those impressions are seen.

00:22:16.960 --> 00:22:19.360
Hence the viewability part.

00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:21.730
Now, in reality, in
the past, if developers

00:22:21.730 --> 00:22:25.330
wanted to guarantee
viewability of their ads,

00:22:25.330 --> 00:22:27.910
they had to integrate
multiple SDKs that

00:22:27.910 --> 00:22:31.420
yielded disparate numbers
of their viewability.

00:22:31.420 --> 00:22:33.370
So to solve that,
what we've done

00:22:33.370 --> 00:22:36.100
is joined an IAB
led coalition, which

00:22:36.100 --> 00:22:39.910
is unifying and simplifying
down to a single methodology

00:22:39.910 --> 00:22:43.840
for measuring
viewability in your ads.

00:22:43.840 --> 00:22:47.140
So we're excited to announce
that we have integrated the IAB

00:22:47.140 --> 00:22:51.730
Open Measurement SDK into
our Google Mobile Ads GMA

00:22:51.730 --> 00:22:56.120
and our Interactive
Media Ads IMA SDKs.

00:22:56.120 --> 00:22:59.320
So this solution will help you
save time as well as reflect

00:22:59.320 --> 00:23:02.290
